Sweden will help set up a waste management project in Eldoret at a cost of Sh500 million.  Officials of the Swedish government led by Ostergotland Governor Elisabeth Nilsson are in Eldoret to hold talks with Uasin Gishu Governor Jackson Mandago on  implementation of the project.   Swedish firm Norrköping Water and Waste will help set up  the  project at the Kipkaren dumpsite and Kipkenyo sewer. Louise Malmström, the  mayor of the Municipality of Norrköping, said Eldoret is beautiful .  Others present are Päivi Johansson (vice mayor of Norrköping,  Henrik Peterson (CEO Norrköping Water and Waste) and Anders Karlsson  also of Norrköping Water. 